cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS 

This paper deals with unsupervised multilingual alignment, which involves finding word-to-word translations between multiple languages without using any parallel data. This problem is related to natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML), which are covered by the cs.CL and cs.LG categories. The proposed method involves using the Wasserstein barycenter, which is a mathematical concept related to optimal transport theory, and optimization techniques, which are covered by the cs.AI and cs.DS categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on standard benchmarks, which involves using computer vision techniques, covered by the cs.CV category. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CL and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.DS.
